author: CNN
description: The Met Museum announced this year's theme for its star-studded annual gala. CNN’s Rachel Tashjian reacts.
title: Met Museum unveils 2026 Met Gala theme

author: CNN
description: A federal judge on Monday scorched the Justice Department’s handling of years-old evidence in its case against former FBI Director James Comey, raising the possibility that US Attorney Lindsey Halligan may have botched the grand jury proceeding and the indictment could be tainted. CNN's Katelyn Polantz reports.
title: Judge says Comey indictment may be tainted

author: CNN
description: An audibly hoarse President Trump told reporters at the White House on Monday that he was “feeling great,” but that he strained his voice while yelling at people over trade. He refused to say which country inspired his ire.
title: Trump says his voice is rough because of shouting at people over trade

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump said he would sign legislation compelling the release of the Justice Department’s Jeffrey Epstein files if it reaches his desk. This comes a day before the House is expected to vote to release the files and after Trump reversed himself and urged GOP lawmakers to support the measure. House Speaker Mike Johnson signaled he could support a bill on releasing the files if changes were made to some provisions in the Senate if the measure heads to the chamber. GOP Senate leader John Thune is still mulling whether to schedule a vote, a source said.

CNN senior White House correspondent Kristen Holmes and CNN anchor and chief Congressional correspondent Manu Raju report, and Kasie Hunt discusses with her "The Arena" panel: political reporter and author Molly Ball, former host of "Hardball" on MSNBC Chris Matthews, CNN political commentator and former communications director for Vice President Harris Jamal Simmons and former GOP congressman from Michigan Peter Meijer. #CN
title: Trump says he would sign bill to release Epstein files

author: CNN
description: Republican Congresswoman Marjorie Taylor Greene, once a staunch ally of President Donald Trump, is now sounding more like Trump's former rival: former Vice President Kamala Harris. CNN's Sunlen Serfaty reports.
title: Marjorie Taylor Greene echoes Kamala Harris

author: CNN
description:
President Trump's approval ratings among Latino voters have plunged between the general elections in 2024 and 2025. CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten breaks down the numbers. 

The Department of Homeland Security's latest targeted immigration blitz began this weekend in Charlotte, NC. A Colombian bakery remains closed after the owner says agents tackled people outside his shop.

CNN's Sara Sidner speaks with Manuel "Manolo" Betancur, who closed his popular Manolo's Bakery in Charlotte as federal agents arrived. #CNN #News
title: Enten: To Latinos, Trump 'is doing something absolutely wrong when it comes to immigration'

author: CNN
description: Tom Cruise showed off his moves on the dance floor with actress and choreographer Debbie Allen as they both celebrated receiving honorary Academy Awards at the 2025 Governors Awards. #CNN #news
title: Video of Tom Cruise dancing goes viral

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Nick Paton Walsh breaks down the possible options for military action in Venezuela that the Trump administration might take.
title: Analysis: Trump's options for US military action in Venezuela

author: CNN
description: A beloved bodega cat named Kit Kat was struck and killed by a Waymo self-driving car on Oct 27 in San Francisco. The death of Kit Kat has outraged the local community and reignited debates over the safety of robotaxis. #cnn #news
title: Death of bodega cat sparks debate over robotaxi safety

author: CNN
description: Bangladesh's ousted prime minister, Sheikh Hasina, has been found guilty of crimes against humanity and was sentenced to death by the International Crimes Tribunal, Bangladesh's domestic war crimes court. Hasina has been staying in self-imposed exile in India since August 2024, after student protesters forced her and her party out of power. CNN's Salma Abdelaziz breaks down why. #cnn #news
title: Bangladesh’s former leader guilty of crimes against humanity

author: CNN
description: Actor Renée Zellweger unveiled a new bronze statue of Bridget Jones in London’s Leicester Square to mark the 25th anniversary of the first film’s release.
title: Renée Zellweger unveils Bridget Jones statue in London

author: CNN
description: In a handful of US states, you can be sued for having an affair that leads to divorce. Recently, a social media influencer was ordered to pay nearly $2 million in damages after a jury found her liable for destroying a couple's marriage. #CNN #news
title: Infidelity at a cost? Influencer ordered to pay $1.75M for affair

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump made a stark reversal and encouraged House Republicans to vote to release more files related to the convicted sex offender Jeffrey Epstein. CNN's Jake Tapper argues this is unnecessary and explains how Trump could order the release of the documents immediately.

#CNN #News #Trump #Epstein #Politics
title: Tapper: Trump’s Epstein reversal is an “exercise in theater”

author: CNN
description: The US has established a coordination center in southern Israel to manage the next phases of the Gaza ceasefire plan, including the planned reconstruction effort and the entry of humanitarian aid. CNN's Oren Liebermann reports from inside the facility.
title: Inside the US military-led facility overseeing next steps for Gaza

author: CNN
description: Italian journalist Gabriele Nunziati says his contract was ended weeks after he asked a Gaza-related question at a European Commission briefing. His former employer denies this and says he didn’t follow editorial guidelines.
title: Journalist claims he was terminated for asking this question

author: CNN
description: Speaking at the Brooklyn Academy of Music, former first lady Michelle Obama responded to a question about the chances of a woman running for president. The comments came as she discussed her new book, "The Look", with host Tracee Ellis Ross.
title: Michelle Obama on the chances of a female president

author: CNN
description: Japan's Sakurajima volcano erupted, creating a cloud of smoke and ash as high as 2.73 miles. The ash fall from the eruption has caused flight cancellations. #cnn #japan #volcano
title: Japanese volcano creates smoke cloud 2.7 miles tall

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump encouraged House Republicans to vote to release the Jeffrey Epstein files and move on from what he calls a “Democrat Hoax,” marking a stark reversal from his efforts to discredit the effort. #cnn #news #epsteinfiles
title: Trump calls on Republicans to release the Epstein files

author: CNN
description: After years of war, the authorities in Benghazi, Libya, are trying to attract international tourists. They've started with a brand new skydiving center. CNN’s Isobel Yeung reports. #cnn #libya #benghazi #skydiving
title: Skydiving in Benghazi

author: CNN
description: China is positioning itself as a leader in the global green transition, sending a large delegation to COP30 and pledging to reduce emissions by up to 10% from their peak by 2035, even as it continues to build coal plants. CNN's Simone McCarthy reports from Beijing. #cnn #news #china #cop30
title: Could the world's biggest polluter be its savior against climate change?

author: CNN
description: Washington announced that it will designate the Venezuelan cartel, Cartel de los Soles, as a foreign terrorist organization, effective November 24, which the US alleges is led by President Nicolás Maduro and other high-ranking officials. CNN's Stefano Pozzebon reports on the latest tensions. #cnn #news #trump #venezuela #maduro #carteldelossoles
title: US to designate Venezuelan cartel as a foreign terrorist organization

author: CNN
description:
From economic insecurity across the country, the breakup with Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene, to a potentially scaled-up military campaign in Venezuela, President Donald Trump is set to return to Washington with a full plate awaiting him. CNN's Betsy Klein has more.

#CNN #News
title: Analysis: Trump faces cracks in MAGA base as he returns to Washington
